1.2 计算 Q 值¶

Q-Learning Q-Learning Value IterationPolicy Iteration-ValueUtility

Q-Learning Q - Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) $$

- $(s_{t},a)$ $a$ $R_{t+1}$ $a$ $s_{t+1}$Q $\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})$$\gamma$

Q $alpha$ Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = (1-\alpha) \times q(s_{t},a) + \alpha \times(R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})) $$

  1. Q Q

3 epsilon-greedy

In [1]:
import random
import numpy as np

actions = ['u','r','d','l']
qline = {'u':1.2, 'r':-2.1, 'd':-24.5, 'l':27}
epsilon = 0.3 # 0.3

def choose_action(epsilon):
    
    random_choose = np.random.choice([1, 0], p=[epsilon, 1 - epsilon])
    if random_choose == 1: # 
        action = random.choice(actions) # 
    else: 
        max_key = max(qline, key=qline.get)
        key_index = list(qline.keys()).index(max_key)
        action = actions[key_index] #  Q 
    return action

from Runner import Runner
def plot_training(maze, epoch, epsilon, alpha, gamma):
    r = Robot(maze, alpha=alpha, epsilon0=epsilon0, gamma=gamma)
    r.set_status(learning=True)

    runner = Runner(r, g)
    runner.run_training(epoch, display_direction=True)
    runner.plot_results()
